<problem>
<!-- <title>differentiate product f(x)=exp(x)*quadratic(x)</title> -->

<setup>

<selectFromSequence assignNames='a' from='1' to=' 7' />
<selectFromSequence assignNames='b c' numberToSelect='2' withReplacement from='-5' to=' 5' />

<math name='answer' simplify='numbers' > (2*$a *x + $b  + $a *x^2+$b *x+$c )*(e^x)</math>
<math name='fun' simplify='numbers' >($a *x^2 + $b *x+$c )* (e^x)</math>
<math name='poly' simplify='numbers' >$a *x^2 + $b *x+$c </math>
<math name='exponential' simplify='numbers' >e^x</math>
<math name='dpoly' simplify='numbers' >2*$a *x+$b </math>
<math name='dexponential' simplify='numbers' >$exponential </math>

</setup>


Compute the derivative, <m>\frac{ df }{ dx }</m>, of the function <m>f(x)</m> below

<me>f(x) = $fun .</me>

<m>f'(x) =</m> 
