<solution>
To calculate the derivative of <m>f(x)=$fun </m>, we need to use the product rule.  The two factors are <m>$poly </m> and <m>$exponential </m>.  By the product rule
<md>
  <mrow>f'(x)\amp = \left($poly \right)' $exponential  + \left($poly \right)\left($exponential \right)'</mrow>
  <mrow>\amp = \left($dpoly \right) $exponential  + \left($poly \right)\left($dexponential \right)</mrow>
  <mrow>\amp = $answer </mrow>
</md>


</solution>


